Basic Node API

# 

<span key="00e5ca2a11a6410f89fd6324afb97886"><span offset-key="00e5ca2a11a6410f89fd6324afb97886:0">Basic Node API</span></span>

<span key="3e27999e332f43dab08ac17b1e93bd93"><span offset-key="3e27999e332f43dab08ac17b1e93bd93:0">Welcome to your </span>`Basic Node API Repository`<span offset-key="3e27999e332f43dab08ac17b1e93bd93:2">. Use this to start your own Greenfield Project using nodejs, express and common industry standards.</span></span>

<span key="f05ea947e3bf4a28af5dba7ca9ec2884"><span offset-key="f05ea947e3bf4a28af5dba7ca9ec2884:0">This repository assumes a handful of industry practices and standards. We strive to keep you up to date in the industry and as a result, we have made some opinions for you so that you don't have to; you're welcome.</span></span>

## 

<span key="8d978f5d87a44860871b8698de692ab6"><span offset-key="8d978f5d87a44860871b8698de692ab6:0">Setup postgres</span></span>

<span key="94e5282c541646b8b04d653f08db6031"><span offset-key="94e5282c541646b8b04d653f08db6031:0">There are 3 options to get postgresql installed locally \[Choose one\]:</span></span>

1.  <span class="r-1awozwy r-1nf4jbm r-6koalj r-18u37iz r-gg6oyi r-ubezar r-16dba41 r-135wba7 r-1m04atk r-1pyaxff" contenteditable="false" style="height:24px">1.</span>
    <span key="a0094911d34b4e12bb7eed7bb33c3692"><span offset-key="a0094911d34b4e12bb7eed7bb33c3692:0">Use docker. </span></span><a href="https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="c49cb1266da2428ebe562095e2be9b0c" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-42229_259-42230-237__"><span data-key="bb373f7041f6433faf2c8e681c24bad3"><span data-offset-key="bb373f7041f6433faf2c8e681c24bad3:0">Install</span></span></span></a><span key="d415c6fc9df2427190e87f54a9722c08"><span offset-key="d415c6fc9df2427190e87f54a9722c08:0"> for your platform</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="b8750436856241e786b840746622fcfb"><span offset-key="b8750436856241e786b840746622fcfb:0">run: </span>`docker-compose up -d`<span offset-key="b8750436856241e786b840746622fcfb:2"> to start up the postgresql database and pgadmin.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="8476ae421295466d814e48420eaeda26"><span offset-key="8476ae421295466d814e48420eaeda26:0">Open a browser to </span></span><a href="http://localhost:5050" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="228eed9839d14cd4a7342fe6c50cd3c6" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-42229_259-42230-237__"><span data-key="58bab621abc14dc6b631e30e562c16e8"><span data-offset-key="58bab621abc14dc6b631e30e562c16e8:0">pgadmin</span></span></span></a><span key="e93565973484402bb8e7323e74b6fb46"><span offset-key="e93565973484402bb8e7323e74b6fb46:0"> and you should see the Dev server already defined.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="21cc91d1da754a24a968268066426416"><span offset-key="21cc91d1da754a24a968268066426416:0">If you need to start over you will need to delete the folder </span>`$ rm -rf ./data/pg`<span offset-key="21cc91d1da754a24a968268066426416:2"> as this is where all of the server data is stored.</span></span>

        -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

            <span key="5f92a7dab20b4e9489541925e69c9251"><span offset-key="5f92a7dab20b4e9489541925e69c9251:0">if the database </span>`api-dev`<span offset-key="5f92a7dab20b4e9489541925e69c9251:2"> was not created then start over.</span></span>

2.  <span class="r-1awozwy r-1nf4jbm r-6koalj r-18u37iz r-gg6oyi r-ubezar r-16dba41 r-135wba7 r-1m04atk r-1pyaxff" contenteditable="false" style="height:24px">2.</span>
    <span key="f090cbb866df498bb3bd90e0c03d668f"><span offset-key="f090cbb866df498bb3bd90e0c03d668f:0">Download and install postgresql directly from the </span></span><a href="https://www.postgresql.org/download/" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="f7e6a71013174636a8e6193510aba020" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-42229_259-42230-237__"><span data-key="a074da46608e4a388aacf2a940bade67"><span data-offset-key="a074da46608e4a388aacf2a940bade67:0">main site</span></span></span></a><span key="3c839aa3ca6d4d0a9ea85c3f90af278b"><span offset-key="3c839aa3ca6d4d0a9ea85c3f90af278b:0">â€‹</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="e97e31823e8e46c1a408362b23a75379"><span offset-key="e97e31823e8e46c1a408362b23a75379:0">make note of the port, username and password you use to setup the database.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="18934e7a79db4647964aa2ec3c145978"><span offset-key="18934e7a79db4647964aa2ec3c145978:0">Connect your client to the server manually using the values previously mentioned</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="7847213942dd4958bffda64a2ebf35c7"><span offset-key="7847213942dd4958bffda64a2ebf35c7:0">You will need to create a database manually using a client.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="8f24b78078304d8b9e33e87aec8f8d5a"><span offset-key="8f24b78078304d8b9e33e87aec8f8d5a:0">Make sure to update the DATABASE\_URL connection string with the values for username/password, databasename and server port (if not 5432).</span></span>

3.  <span class="r-1awozwy r-1nf4jbm r-6koalj r-18u37iz r-gg6oyi r-ubezar r-16dba41 r-135wba7 r-1m04atk r-1pyaxff" contenteditable="false" style="height:24px">3.</span>
    <span key="a6f7fae5952a4ab4a5e7e196bbb1a127"><span offset-key="a6f7fae5952a4ab4a5e7e196bbb1a127:0">Setup a free account at </span></span><a href="https://www.elephantsql.com/plans.html" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="13fc28ac815344d289d8c27d8cff5c5f" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-42229_259-42230-237__"><span data-key="79fe695bf1f8460bacee32a7c909d1e6"><span data-offset-key="79fe695bf1f8460bacee32a7c909d1e6:0">ElephantSQL</span></span></span></a><span key="c3d12cb137ea4a43b3bd0bd40136b2ba"><span offset-key="c3d12cb137ea4a43b3bd0bd40136b2ba:0">â€‹</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="88d6dc31c4544447b299d9eb5e3f5a6e"><span offset-key="88d6dc31c4544447b299d9eb5e3f5a6e:0">Sign up for a free </span>`Tiney Turtle`<span offset-key="88d6dc31c4544447b299d9eb5e3f5a6e:2"> plan</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="b39ff114622e4e61b95c9eb822583d41"><span offset-key="b39ff114622e4e61b95c9eb822583d41:0">copy the URL to the DATABASE\_URL .env variable</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="52139521ef674ebeb6ff897a5f174a0c"><span offset-key="52139521ef674ebeb6ff897a5f174a0c:0">make sure to add </span>`?ssl=true`<span offset-key="52139521ef674ebeb6ff897a5f174a0c:2"> to the end of this url</span></span>

## 

<span key="c2d8506406294acdb58fe77fdc07a10b"><span offset-key="c2d8506406294acdb58fe77fdc07a10b:0">Setup the application</span></span>

<span key="68935b3120504542a16454af78295921"><span offset-key="68935b3120504542a16454af78295921:0">From your project locally run the following commands:</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="64076d5345fb48629ebb3a887ab34c3f"><span offset-key="64076d5345fb48629ebb3a887ab34c3f:0">run: </span>`npm install`<span offset-key="64076d5345fb48629ebb3a887ab34c3f:2"> to download all dependencies.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="522680730ab147049df5e176a461a345"><span offset-key="522680730ab147049df5e176a461a345:0">run: </span>`cp .env.sample .env`<span offset-key="522680730ab147049df5e176a461a345:2"> and update the enviornment variables to match your local setup.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="5472fb1f562b4fb9a9c6704bb4387fe0"><span offset-key="5472fb1f562b4fb9a9c6704bb4387fe0:0">run: </span>`npm run knex migrate:latest`<span offset-key="5472fb1f562b4fb9a9c6704bb4387fe0:2"> to create the starting schema.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="211d63f743074f1b805b57521e07d6ed"><span offset-key="211d63f743074f1b805b57521e07d6ed:0">run: </span>`npm run knex seed:run`<span offset-key="211d63f743074f1b805b57521e07d6ed:2"> to populate your db with some data.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="88dd73060f414ec3b7062bc336bcc95e"><span offset-key="88dd73060f414ec3b7062bc336bcc95e:0">run: </span>`npm run tests`<span offset-key="88dd73060f414ec3b7062bc336bcc95e:2"> to confirm all is setup and tests pass.</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="f0a564b5c4624b629e5222a9b885f221"><span offset-key="f0a564b5c4624b629e5222a9b885f221:0">run: </span>`npm run watch:dev`<span offset-key="f0a564b5c4624b629e5222a9b885f221:2"> to start nodemon in local dev enviornment.</span></span>

<span key="7a9cab9f77d74cf0a338f6483409e0df"><span offset-key="7a9cab9f77d74cf0a338f6483409e0df:0">Make sure to update the details of the app name, description and version in the </span>`package.json`<span offset-key="7a9cab9f77d74cf0a338f6483409e0df:2"> and </span>`config/jsdoc.js`<span offset-key="7a9cab9f77d74cf0a338f6483409e0df:4"> files.</span></span>
